               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="person_287984736">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Mxt_1408-item1">
                     <author key="person_f4896">
                        <persName type="supplied" subtype="aut">ʾIbrāhīm al-Kīshīإبراهيم الكيشي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7762">وسائل الوصول إلى مسائل الفصول</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7762">Means to Arrive at the Questions about the Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="alt" key="work_7762">Wasāʼl al-Wuṣūl ilā Masāʼil al-Fuṣūl</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript held at Austrian National Library, Österreichische Nationalbibliothek.</note>
                     <note>This MS claims to be <persName type="supplied" key="person_f1991">Kīshī</persName> ’s commentary rather than a gloss by <persName type="supplied" key="person_f5647">‘Abd al-Raḥmān al-Ṭabīb</persName>. Based on a survey of Vi1, it appears that Kīshī’s work is not a commentary (sharḥ) as much as a paraphrase of each aphorism. The introduction begins on <locus>f. 57b</locus>. The beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk1: <locus>57b</locus>; Bk2: <locus>58b</locus>; Bk3: <locus>59b</locus>; Bk4: <locus>61a</locus>; Bk5: <locus>62b</locus>; Bk6: <locus>64b</locus>; Bk7: <locus>65a</locus>. Since it is a gloss, it is not clear whether it contains all of al-Kīshī’s text. The aphorisms are not cited verbatim, and commentaries on several aphorisms are omitted.</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <author ref="viaf.org/viaf/37439401" key="person_37439401">Helene Loebenstein</author>
                           <date calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1970" notAfter="1970">1970</date>, <title>Katalog der arabischen Handschriften der Österreichischen Nationalbibliothek: Neuerwerbungen <date calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1868" notAfter="1968">1868-1968</date> 1: Codices mixti ab Nr 74</title>
